Physics 137b: Quantum Mechanics Part II (undergraduate course). 
Course instructor: Professor Petr Horava.
Topics:
1. Approximation methods (for time-dependent and time-independent problems);
2. Identical particles and quantum statistics;
3. Interaction of quantum systems with electromagnetism (both as radiation and as external field);
4. Quantum collision theory and scattering;
5. Bonus material: an introduction to quantum field theory.
Text: Quantum Mechanics, 2nd Ed. by B.H. Bransden and C.J. Joachain.

Physics 232a: Quantum Field Theory I (graduate course). 
Course instructor: Professor Petr Horava.
Topics: 
1. Path integrals; 
2. Canonical quantization of scalar, electromagnetic, and Dirac fields; 
3. Derivation of Feynman rules; 
4. Regularization, renormalization, and the renormalization group; 
5. Spontaneous symmetry breaking and the Higgs mechanism. 
Texts: An Introduction to Quantum Field Theory by M. Peskin and D. Schroeder; and Quantum Field Theory in a Nutshell, 2nd Ed. by A. Zee.

